15 bool PandaJointVelocityController::init(hardware_interface::RobotHW* robot_hardware,
16  ros::NodeHandle& node_handle) {
17  velocity_joint_interface_ = robot_hardware->get<hardware_interface::VelocityJointInterface>();
18  if (velocity_joint_interface_ == nullptr) {
19  ROS_ERROR(
20  "PandaJointVelocityController: Error getting velocity joint interface from hardware!");
21  return false;
22  }
23  std::vector<std::string> joint_names;
24  if (!node_handle.getParam("joint_names", joint_names)) {
25  ROS_ERROR("PandaJointVelocityController: Could not parse joint names");
26  }
27  if (joint_names.size() != 7) {
28  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("PandaJointVelocityController: Wrong number of joint names, got "
29  << joint_names.size() << " instead of 7 names!");
30  return false;
31  }
32 
33  velocity_joint_handles_.resize(7);
34  for (size_t i = 0; i < 7; ++i) {
35  try {
36  velocity_joint_handles_[i] = velocity_joint_interface_->getHandle(joint_names[i]);
37  } catch (const hardware_interface::HardwareInterfaceException& ex) {
38  ROS_ERROR_STREAM(
39  "PandaJointVelocityController: Exception getting joint handles: " << ex.what());
40  return false;
41  }
42  }
43 
44  for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
45  joint_velocities[i] = 0.0;
46  }
47 
48  last_time_called = ros::Time::now().toSec();
49 
50  sub_command_ = node_handle.subscribe<std_msgs::Float64MultiArray>("command", 10, &PandaJointVelocityController::jointCommandCb, this);
51 
52  std::string arm_id;
53  if (!node_handle.getParam("arm_id", arm_id)) {
54  ROS_ERROR("PandaJointVelocityController: Could not read parameter arm_id");
55  return false;
56  }
57  auto* state_interface = robot_hardware->get<franka_hw::FrankaStateInterface>();
58  if (state_interface == nullptr) {
59  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("PandaJointVelocityController: Error getting state interface from hardware");
60  return false;
61  }
62  try {
63  state_handle_ = std::make_unique<franka_hw::FrankaStateHandle>(
64  state_interface->getHandle(arm_id + "_robot"));
65  } catch (hardware_interface::HardwareInterfaceException& ex) {
66  ROS_ERROR_STREAM(
67  "PandaJointVelocityController: Exception getting state handle from interface: " << ex.what());
68  return false;
69  }
70 
71  return true;
72 }

77 void PandaJointVelocityController::update(const ros::Time& time,
78  const ros::Duration& period) {
79  // Get current Franka::RobotState
80  franka::RobotState robot_state = state_handle_->getRobotState();
81 
82  // If there is no command for more than 0.1 sec, set velocity to 0.0
83  if (ros::Time::now().toSec() - last_time_called > 0.1) {
84  for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++) velocity_joint_handles_[i].setCommand(0.0);
85  } else { // If command recieved, send the command to the controller
86  for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
87  // Print out to the terminal just for the 1st joint for debugging.
88  // Order: Commanded Joint Velocity << Acutal Commanded Joint Velocity << Current Joint Velocity
89  // if (i == 0) ROS_INFO_STREAM("Panda_joint" << i+1 << " " << joint_velocities[i] << " " << robot_state.dq_d[i] << " " << robot_state.dq[i]);
90  // Send command
91  velocity_joint_handles_[i].setCommand(joint_velocities[i]);
92  }
93  }
94 }

96 void PandaJointVelocityController::stopping(const ros::Time& /*time*/) {
97  // WARNING: DO NOT SEND ZERO VELOCITIES HERE AS IN CASE OF ABORTING DURING MOTION
98  // A JUMP TO ZERO WILL BE COMMANDED PUTTING HIGH LOADS ON THE ROBOT. LET THE DEFAULT
99  // BUILT-IN STOPPING BEHAVIOR SLOW DOWN THE ROBOT.
100 }
101 
102 void PandaJointVelocityController::jointCommandCb(const std_msgs::Float64MultiArray::ConstPtr& joint_velocity_commands) {
103  if (joint_velocity_commands->data.size() != 7) {
104  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("PandaJointVelocityController: Wrong number of joint velocity commands, got "
105  << joint_velocity_commands->data.size() << " instead of 7 commands!");
106  }
107 
108  // Receive Joint Velocity Commands from a topic and save them in joint_velocities.
109  for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++) joint_velocities[i] = joint_velocity_commands->data[i];
110  // Save the time when the last topic was published
111  last_time_called = ros::Time::now().toSec();
112 }
